  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: working tree clean, branch `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes, tasks 031â€“034 all âś…. Load knowledge. Declare RIGOR LEVEL: FULL.</step>
    <step order="1">Read all 4 resolver implementations (031â€“034). Trace Pending-state storage for each â€” identify all sweep targets. Confirm the contract: resolvers populate `GateRequest.TimeoutSeconds` from `Action.governance.gateTimeoutSeconds` (or default 300).</step>
    <step order="2">Create `GateTimeoutServiceOptions.cs` â€” POCO with `SweepIntervalSeconds` (default 30) + `DefaultTimeoutSeconds` (default 300). Bind from `appsettings.json` section `ActionEngine:GateTimeoutService`.</step>
    <step order="3">Add `ExpirePendingAsync(TimeSpan maxAge, CancellationToken ct)` to `IGateApprovalChannel` (task 032). Implementation in `SseGateApprovalChannel`: iterate dictionary, flip TCS to `TimedOut` for entries where `now - createdAt > maxAge`. Returns count of flipped entries. Add corresponding unit test.</step>
    <step order="4">Create `GateTimeoutService.cs` â€” `BackgroundService` with periodic loop. Each iteration:
      (a) Query `sprk_gate_approval` for Pending records past `CreatedAtUtc + TimeoutSeconds`. Update each to `TimedOut` with optimistic concurrency (`If-Match` etag). Audit each via `IAuditService.LogGateDecision(GateDecision.TimedOut, reason: "auto-rejected after timeout")`.
      (b) Call `IGateApprovalChannel.ExpirePendingAsync(MaxAge)`. For each flipped TCS, audit `TimedOut`.
      (c) Emit App Insights `gate_engine.timeout_fired` custom event per outcome + `gate_engine.pending_count` metric per iteration.
      (d) `await Task.Delay(SweepIntervalSeconds, stoppingToken)`. Handle `OperationCanceledException` gracefully.</step>
    <step order="5">Register DI in `AddGatesFeature()`: `services.Configure&lt;GateTimeoutServiceOptions&gt;(...); services.AddHostedService&lt;GateTimeoutService&gt;();`. Update `phase3-di-budget.md` running tally (now ~12 of 15).</step>
    <step order="6">Update each resolver (031â€“034) to read `Action.governance.gateTimeoutSeconds` (if set) when constructing the `GateRequest` they pass to the channel/Dataverse. Use `GateTimeoutServiceOptions.DefaultTimeoutSeconds` as the fallback. Minimal-diff edits; do NOT change resolver behavior beyond timeout-value population.</step>
    <step order="7">Write integration test suite `ActionEngine.IntegrationTests.GateResolution` covering:
      (a) `DataverseQueueGateResolver_TimesOut_AfterConfiguredSeconds` â€” create Action with `gateTimeoutSeconds=5`; invoke gate; advance time (or actual wait in short-window test); assert sweep updates record + audit.
      (b) `InteractiveInChatGateResolver_TimesOut_AfterConfiguredSeconds` â€” invoke; never POST to respond endpoint; assert sweep resolves TCS + outcome = `TimedOut` + audit.
      (c) `WebhookGateResolver_TimesOut_AfterConfiguredSeconds` â€” invoke; never callback; assert sweep covers webhook pending state + audit. Coordinate with task 033 storage decision.
      (d) `AutoApproveGateResolver_NoTimeoutPath_AlwaysImmediate` â€” invoke; assert synchronous `Approved` (no Pending state, sweep has nothing to do).
      (e) `MultiInstance_Idempotent_OptimisticConcurrency` â€” simulate two sweep instances racing on same Dataverse record; assert exactly one timeout audit emitted, second instance no-ops cleanly.
      (f) `Audit_TimedOutOutcome_LoggedWithReason` â€” assert audit contains `Reason = "auto-rejected after timeout"` and `GateDecision = TimedOut`.</step>
    <step order="8">Build + run tests: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` exits 0; `dotnet test tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/` passes new suite. Use short timeout values (e.g., 5 sec) in tests for fast feedback; sweep interval also reduced for tests via test-overridden options.</step>
    <step order="9">Measure publish-size delta; expect &lt; 0.1 MB. Record in `notes/measurements/035-publish-size-delta.md`. Phase 3 cumulative delta: sum of 030â€“035 deltas; record cumulative in same file.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` (multi-instance idempotency correctness; sweep interval not too aggressive; audit ordering; observability metric naming), `adr-check` (ADR-001/004/009/010/013/015/029).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: 035 âś…. Update `current-task.md`. Mark Phase 3 ~60% complete (still pending: 036 GateApprovalCard). G3 graduation gate verified by `GateResolutionTests` suite passing.</step>
    <step order="11">Commit + push. Document any contract refinements in `notes/decisions/035-timeout-sweep-design.md` (interval, multi-instance handling, observability).</step>
  </steps>

