  <notes>
    Multi-instance idempotency is the highest-risk correctness axis. Two options:
    - **Optimistic concurrency** (`If-Match` etag on Dataverse update): minimal new infrastructure; sweep loses race â†’ no-op; audit emitted only by winning instance.
    - **`IDistributedLock` (Redis)**: heavier-weight; only needed if optimistic concurrency proves insufficient.

    Default to optimistic concurrency; document trade-off in `notes/decisions/035-timeout-sweep-design.md`.

    Test infrastructure: short timeout values (5â€“10 sec) avoid wall-clock test latency. If your CI/CD runner is slow, override options via test-startup config. Avoid `Thread.Sleep` in tests â€” use a controllable clock abstraction (`TimeProvider` per .NET 8) for deterministic time advancement.

    The G3 graduation gate test suite (`GateResolutionTests`) is the canonical artifact cited by Phase 6 task 062 (G3 verification). DO NOT inline the timeout assertions only into per-resolver tests â€” the unified integration suite IS the gate.

    Observability metric naming follows `action_engine.*` namespace per spec NFR-07; `gate_engine.*` here is a deliberate sub-namespace for gate-specific telemetry. Coordinate with Phase 6 dashboard task if any.
  </notes>

